The Trinity Access Programme in conjunction with the Equality Fund is running an event in Front Square on the 5th of April at 1pm, the event is called a Privilege Walk and can be seen here. 
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=hD5f8GuNuGQ 

The aim of this event is to increase awareness of where privilege can place people. Every statement addresses some small privilege that is based on gender, race, ethnicity, ability, class, or sexual orientation. The small statements in this exercise will add up to divide people into different locations across front square. This will reflect how small privileges in society often place individuals in different places in society. 
Interestingly, privilege tends to be invisible to those who are privileged. That is, when we receive privilege based on race, gender, ethnicity, ability, sexual orientation or any other factor, we tend to not recognize the boosts in position that accumulate over time from those privileges. The point of this exercise is not to make any of us embarrassed about the privileges we have received, but to make all of us aware of how privilege based on gender, race, etc function. Whether we are highly privileged, moderately privileged or lack privilege, it is possible to behave in ways that level the playing field for everyone

To sign up can you please contact president@tcdsu.org

всем привет ! 

Before we all finish up for the year , we would like to announce our final event !

We are holding our AGM in the Global room on Thursday 7th of April from 19:00-21:00. We invite all who have an interest in Russian culture and language to come along ! All committee positions will be available and we highly suggest you get involved ! We have had some highly successful and fun events this year and would like this to continue , so come along and make it happen ! :) 

These are the guidelines ; 
Any ordinary member of the Society is eligible to run for the commitee positions. In order to run, a member must be nominated by another ordinary member of the society at the AGM. 

Each candidate will be offered a brief window of 1-2 minutes to address members to explain why they feel they are suitable for the position, before voting begins. 

Elections will be run by secret ballot , with the successful candidate being the one to achieve a simple majority of votes. Members ,may run in multiple elections at the AGM. 

Please note that membership cards will be checked as members enter the AGM against and up-to-date list of members. No new members will be admitted less than 24 hours prior to the AGM. You will be unable to receive a ballot paper if you are not a member, with both a membership card and your name on the membership list. 

If you have any questions , please don't hesitate to get in touch!

Have a good one :) 

Russian Society TCD
